modules.description: Checks if a string matches a specified pattern, applying a given action and callback function upon success. Works with strings and custom action identifiers. Used to validate user input against predefined rules in a command-line interface.

Converts theme and data size values to human-readable strings, and validates input parameters against specified constraints, applying a provided callback on success. Operates on custom types representing themes and data sizes. Used to enforce configuration rules during system initialization.

Handles reCAPTCHA verification and site key generation using HTTP requests. Accepts secret keys, site keys, and user responses as strings, and interacts with reCAPTCHA's API endpoints. Processes JSON responses to validate user interactions and confirm site ownership.
